<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[264,1324,1567,1873]" lastBlockId="19.[264,1322,284,390]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis box="[264,374,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
There is a problem with the nomenclature of this well­known and widely distributed species as there appears to be an older name, 
<taxonomicName authority="Forskal, 1775" authorityName="Forskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[868,1264,1607,1633]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[868,1090,1607,1632]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Cancer tridentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Forskal" box="[1098,1264,1607,1633]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refString="Forskal, P. (1775) Descriptiones Animalium, Avium, Amphibiorum, Piscium, Insectorum, Vermium. Hafniae, 19 + xxxii + 164 pp." type="book" year="1775">
Forskål, 
<number box="[1202,1264,1607,1633]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Forskal, 1775" authorityName="Forskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[532,921,1647,1673]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[532,753,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Cancer tridentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Forskal" box="[760,921,1647,1673]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refString="Forskal, P. (1775) Descriptiones Animalium, Avium, Amphibiorum, Piscium, Insectorum, Vermium. Hafniae, 19 + xxxii + 164 pp." type="book" year="1775">
Forskål, 
<number box="[862,921,1647,1673]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(from Suez, Red Sea), is too brief to be certain of its identity, but as it is, it fits the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[922,1028,1687,1712]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[922,1028,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Domecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as presently understood. The description best fits 
<taxonomicName authority="Eydoux and Souleyet, 1842" authorityName="Eydoux and Souleyet" authorityYear="1842" box="[555,1090,1727,1753]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis box="[555,754,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Domecia hispida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Eydoux" box="[762,1090,1727,1753]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refString="Eydoux, F. &amp; Souleyet, F. A. (1842) Crustaces. In: Voyage autour du monde execute pendant les annees 1836 et 1837 sur la corvette la Bonite, commandee par M. Vaillant. Zoologie, 1 (2), 107 - 328; Atlas, pls. 1 - 150." type="journal article" year="1842">
Eydoux and Souleyet, 
<number box="[1028,1090,1727,1753]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1842.0">1842</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is present in the Red Sea. As Forskål's material is no longer extant, we can never be certain. However, to have the senior name replacing the widely used name of 
<taxonomicName box="[956,1156,1807,1832]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis box="[956,1156,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Domecia hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
serves no real purpose in our opinion, and we invoke Article 23.9. 
<number box="[866,881,1847,1873]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
of the current zoological code in suppressing the senior name. Certainly, the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Forskal, 1775" authorityName="Forskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[806,1198,284,310]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis box="[806,1027,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cancer tridentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Forskal" box="[1035,1198,284,310]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Forskal, P. (1775) Descriptiones Animalium, Avium, Amphibiorum, Piscium, Insectorum, Vermium. Hafniae, 19 + xxxii + 164 pp." type="book" year="1775">
Forskål, 
<number box="[1137,1198,284,310]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, has never been used since its description while the name 
<taxonomicName box="[830,1031,324,349]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis box="[830,1031,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Domecia hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been regularly used over the last few decades.
</paragraph>
